caption: Very neat and welcoming place. They offer large portions and for fair prices. I enjoyed the food a lot and the staff members were super attentive and informative. Will definitely recommend this spot.
The waitstaff make you feel like a member of their family. The food and mixed drinks are better than my grasp of the english language can describe. I can't wait for my next experience there!
Delicious food and drink
hmmm well my french toast was a little burnt. hubby had hamburger hangover was basic.

So disappointed, we have been fans of wine kitchen.  It is one of our favorite spots to go.  We had reservations for new years and they called us back after we made reservations and told us that they would only have a set menu.  So no problem right? Well the 6 course meal was 100 dollars! Still not a problem, but they offered frog legs, and small dishes.  The gentleman who spoke to us who was the manager was rude and was more interested in selling wine for the night.  I can tell you we have personally been to wine kitchen over 20 times and refer tons of people to them, I think we will have to find a new favorite spot.  Not because of what they offered but because of the rude manger.
The dessert was just.... wow..... I mean I have no words to describe how good it was. In fact, I might go right now just for this dessert...

I have been here a few times now, I am typically blown away from the staffs level of knowledge and the decedance of the food. This restaurant food is usually amazing and the staff is typically very friendly and eager to help those who may be newer to this level of dining.  On my last visit, while the service was above par I was less impressed with the food I have had in the past. This past visit I ordered the butchers special which happened to be lamb. Lamb is a favorite of mine if prepared and cooked correctly. Unfortunately the lamb fell short of my expectations.  In the past I have had amazing dishes here. And while I could tell the lamb was prepared with care whomever was cooking did not execute the dish as I had hoped. I'm sure I will be back as the food was still good. It was just not amazing as it had been in the past. Time and taste will tell if this was a fluke or the new norm for the wine kitchen.
Would certainly recommend trying out this place. Fantastic atmosphere, delicious food, great customer service. Kudos.
This was a great experience  the food and drink selection are great. We also enjoyed  eating outside. Also the staff was amazing and very helpful
They really made my birthday special!  🎂 Excellent food!  Try the venison!!

I live in Frederick and go at least a few times a year. I find the food to be great, meanwhile the service is hit or miss--too expensive of a restaurant to have hit or miss service. We spent 10 minutes looking over the menu only for the server to tell us they were out of specific entrees AFTER my husband ordered one of them. Why not tell us when we were handed our menus?  Overall server acted as if she was going out of her way to wait on us. Not at all personable, never came back to ask how our food was or if we wanted more wine, and when she asked if I liked a soup (oh, how nice of you to care), I said it I didn't love it, explained why, and she came back and with a bit of an edge (although maybe this was just her personality) said that they only charged us for half of the cost of the soup. I had not even asked them to do this.  Everything was just off this evening. One couple got up and left, another table complained about their service as well. I'm in no hurry to go back anytime soon.  EDIT (sorry this took so long to edit) - owner reached out after I posted and sent a gift card and it was so appreciated. We've since returned and have eaten out with them several times during COVID to support local restaurants. As a matter of fact, just last night we carried out dinner. The chicken cassoulet was AH-MA-ZING. Thank you!
Best service I've had in a restaurant. Delicious food.
Wonderful place loved the food and wine. Very polite and informative staff. This is our first time but we got a warm welcome. Limited menu but has most of them. Very good dessert. Recommended.
Normally love this place, but what a shame they shut down online ordering for New Year’s Eve 2020. As if to encourage people to dine in? During COVID? Extremely disappointed.

AMAZING EXPERIENCE!!  My husband and I found this place on Google and made a reservation on a whim!  Our reservation was at 3pm, just as lunch was ending and surprisingly, Happy Hour was beginning!!  We just wanted something light but “nice”, so we ordered the charcuterie board and it outstanding!!  Sam, the server is the ONLY way to go. The team work is evident and it I plan to share with all of my friends in the area.  We live 25 min away and it was well worth it!!
The mushroom strudel is simply amazing! They have done a good job with social distancing and keeping you safe. They have the cutest bag to store your mask on the table.
The 💣
Good food and great wine.
Top quality food at below top quality prices.
Amazing place. Some of the best wine around. You won’t be disappointed
Not the wine kitchen pre-Covid.  It was terrible the food tasted sub par and the wine selection was awful.

I celebrated my graduation earlier this evening in this great place. I am glad to say that we passed a phenomenal evening and the restaurant was absolutely one of the reasons for that fruitful celebration. The stuff  collaborated in a pleasant manner, the cuisine was great and my guests were extremely  happy. We shall absolutely visit again for more events. Thank you very much.
The wait staff and the food were both phenomenal.

Great wine selection however, the lunch menu is scarce. We live pretty far away ( 1/12 hrs ) so the chance of me coming back for the dinner menu after the lunch menu options , pretty slim to none. My bf hamburger tasted good! Sometimes, you just don't want a burger. 🙃
service is excellent even when they are busy. the service was helpful and kind. the bill was decent.

The waygu burger was delicious as well as the short ribs. One item in the kids menu called the pastry pizza was a little too sophisticated for our 6 year old, but the adults liked it. So the food is very tasty,  but the service is even better! Also, the views from the patio are the best. We sat outside and enjoyed a beautiful autumn afternoon. The staff is excellent at following safety protocols and make you feel very comfortable. There's even a hand sanitizer pump at every table. They also offer contact-less menus as well as payment. Wonderful experience overall.
Excellent charcuterie and service. The view was amazing! If you're into flights this is THE place for you! Whiskey and wine flights are a nice touch.
Absolutely divine food and drinks! The wait staff was top notch and we so enjoyed ourselves we stayed thru dessert!

Great place to have a meal with outside patio seating overlooking the creek. Went for dinner and got the fried green tomatoes, beets, mac and cheese, and the butternut squash mignon (pictured). All tastes great with our favorite was the squash and fried green tomatoes. Will definitely visit here again.

This has always been my favorite lunch spot in Frederick.  I went for the first time since the pandemic started this week. They have special coverings on the door handle, hand sanitizer on each table and little bags to hold you mask while you eat. They sanitize each table between customers.  They have contactless menus and receipts.  Service and food were also fantastic. The Wagyu burger is great.  Also love the wine descriptions.
Had a lovely birthday dinner with Phil as our server. Perfection.
The mussels are a must have.

Pretty flawless experience all around. We tried everything from a vegetarian "mignon" to whiskey choices, red wine and venison. Not one issue with the service or food quality, venison was slightly undercooked but still tasted delicious. Perhaps my highlight was the option for america , scotch or japanese whiskey flights.  Recommended.
Food is delish and the location is perfect to experience the beauty of Frederick.
Fabulous food, friendly staff, and the most picturesque location on Carroll Creek.  What a delightful place to lunch with a friend!
Why can't I give this place 10 stars!? Always a great experience with great food, meats, cheeses and of course, wine. What a treat this place is!

I am editing my review from 4 years ago when we had to leave due to issues with the kitchen and staff.  I recently returned and was extremely happy with the changes the management have made, as well as the personal attention from the staff.  The food and atmosphere were excellent, and the staff went above and beyond for all patrons.  We had a great time and will return.

Great view and scene! Beautiful plant umbrella above my head. So the plant umbrella was made from wire that has a vine growing on it. Gorgeous canal area.  I like to eat vegan and ordered the “steak” entree. It had a lot of flavor.  Coffee was yummy and could use coconut milk as my creamer.  Staff wore matching tie dye shirts and were pleasant and attentive our needs.  The ice tea was delicious and had hints of peach in it. I ordered the unsweetened option.  The fried green tomatoes were quite good too. Be careful the first bite may be hot temperature wise.  Parking and finding the restaurant was tough. I parked in a massive garage near the library. Therefore the third floor on the parking garage. I paid $3. I could not see the restaurant from where I parked and I had to walk a waze to find the spot, which was a bit uncomfortable bc I did not know where I was going.
Excellent drinks....tasty flights of wine with info on the wine....food was decent.  Worth a stop just for the beautiful view.

Great decor and intimate place to dine, but the food takes too long. Wanted to give the restaurant a chance for restaurant week, but after the appetizer came, I waited 30 minutes for a burger. Very ridiculous and the place was not that busy. Would not recommend if you don't have all day to wait. Still waiting on my food.....

My Husband and I made a reservation for August 9th through Google/open table reservations.  We made a notation that we would like an outside seat.  We arrived on time and noticed that all the outside tables were taken.  When I asked the Host how long the wait would be he said and hour or more.   Before I go on I do want to say the the host was very polite and professional.  However, I did ask how can the wait be so long if I have a reservation.  He advised that they do not hold reservations for outside tables.   I was confused as I specifically requested an outside table.  He offered to get the manager so she can explain.    The Manager did come out and she seemed agitated and defensive during the discussion.  She falsely stated that the reservation sites (open table and google reservations) clearly state outdoor dining is unavailable.  They do not and I even went back to check to see if I overlooked this.  She stated we have never held reservations for out side, but I know that to be untrue as I have done this before and was seated outside immediately.    But more disconcerting the manager made no offer to make things right.  No offer to place us at the next available outside table to compensate for the confusion.  Her excuse was we did not notice your request.  We ended up leaving and cancelling our reservation.   To put icing on the cake her last sarcastic words to me were "have a great life".
Great atmosphere and good food and drinks

the Wine Kitchen features great food, great service in a comfortable atmosphere.  Wine by the bottle, flight, or glass with enough depth and variety to keep it interesting.  The menu changes often with even the specials updated even more frequently.  Loved their caesar salad with smoked trout, hope that comes back.  I take my kids there as often as I can without feeling guilty.  It’s a block from my office and pretty close to home along the very scenic Carroll Creek in downtown historic Frederick.
Really good value.
Slow service. Food okay at best.  May be pricier that normal for what u get

When I was in a cast, they were very accommodating. The charcuterie board was excellent, but the French Toast was so so sweet. This is still 5 stars though because the waitress immediately took it off the bill and let us order something else. Also, the apple butter is ANAZING!
Our first visit was beyond our expectations! The burger was delicious, the wine selection was phenomenal, and the cocktails were perfectly prepared. Definitely need to go back soon!

Not only was the food and drink amazing but the staff was so accommodating and friendly.  We came in not to far from closing time and never felt rushed or unwelcome.  Also the view was beautiful sitting on the creek.  Will be back for sure.
Always delicious, always consistent.
Class A service - with affordable quality.

You may find the menu pricing on the expensive side but I think is worth it, they make a good job working with local source produce, you can definitely taste the quality of their food and great selection of wines.
Food was great and front end staff was very polite

We reserved their private dining area for after wedding dinner, with reception following the next evening at another location. The room was a perfect space. The wait staff were outstanding and on top of everything.  The dinner menus we selected were delicious, the food fresh. Thanks for an awesome evening!
This spot has awesome service as well as delicious meals. One of my favourite spots around here. The drinks and food arrived fast and the prices are economical. I recommend this place.
Wonderful food. Great service and atmosphere
Good food, nice atmosphere. This is quality, fine dining with a price tag.
Tasty as always, yet could have been more inventive. They displayed their usual veg dish, which could be modified as vegan. Would have been nice to be something new.
Great steaks and atmosphere. Patio is perfect on the creek.
Amazing food and great happy hour! Friendly and accommodating staff!
Very delicious and a lot of attention to detail.
Amazing charcuterie platter,  terrific service and atmosphere

Now this is a special place for great and tasty food, professional service, and wine. Loved the wine tasting at the table. It made our date, so much more experiential and fun. Everything is first class.

Excellent wine, food, and courteous staff. From the moment we walked into the door until the moment we left, we were welcomed and made to feel at home. The food was phenomenal and the wine selection was great.
Always have a good time at The Kitchen.  Thursday $1 oysters are a must!
Great service, really great food.
The outdoor seating on a nice warm day is the best. Wine and food delicious

Went for brunch as a party of 5 to celebrate a loved ones birthday. The food was immaculate! Our server was very knowledgeable and able to answer any questions we had. Will definitely be back for my next special occasion.
Excellent food and wine! Bar menu half price during happy hour!! Definitely worth full price!!!
I tried this spot already with a friend and I am obsessed ever since. I enjoy the good atmosphere and flavorful food and drinks. Kudos.
Great atmosphere and service. Very nice ribeye and good wine selection.
Very very good, we ate brunch. The food was excellent and so was the service. The noise level was low enough to tak across the table without yelling and the overall ambiance was nice

Apparently walk ins aren't allowed... me and my wife went there around 6pm with our baby. Was told by the host that if we didn't have a reservation we couldn't eat there. Really? Didn't see that anywhere on their website or in any reviews. I find it hard to believe that we couldn't wait for a table... Maybe the host just didn't want a couple with a baby in the restaurant. Either way really disappointed we couldn't eat there. We drove an hour to try this restaurant.
Would definitely recommend trying this place. Awesome mood, delicious food, fantastic customer service. I recommend this place.

Had a nice upbeat vibe, good food and great service. Staff very knowledgeable about the wines and the various dishes. Chef closely supervised, we could observe him somewhat in the open kitchen. Tried a wine flight and the descriptor card was a bit ridiculous, not terribly helpful if your aim is to expand your tasting skills but they were fun to read to others at the table and the wine was good. It is a pricey, multi course experience with very rich and well prepared dishes, we found we were happily there for nearly 3 hours.  We will return for special occasions and did really enjoy our evening which included a walk along Carroll Creek right outside the door.
Wonderful lunch. Delicious food. Great staff. Cocktails, spirit and wine offerings....just wow. Can't beat it. And reasonably priced too. Looking forward to more meals here.

Excellent food and service. New American is well displayed. We had a variety of dishes, each top notch. The service was fantastic.  A little confusing to find from the street side, but easy from the canal side.
Great food and always accommodating.  Can become overly crowded and cold inside.
Fantastic spot to eat some food when in a rush. Their customer service is prompt, prices are reasonable, awesome mood. Will come visit again

Tried the buffalo chicken fries w the bleu cheese mousse. The fries and the mousse were excellent! The buffalo chicken was really salty for some reason.   I also had the steak salad niçoise, medium.  It was awesome. I dipped my steak in some leftover Bleu cheese mousse.  Blasphemy I know but it was DEEE LISH OUS!!  No pics though. Sorry.
The steaks are amazing, the wine choices are superb. It's a bit pricey so put some extra cash in your wallet.

I took my daughter here for her 31st birthday. The entire experience was fabulous and the service was second to none. We felt like we had an entire team taking care of us. Hayden and Justin made the evening a 5 star experience... Thanks again guys!

The service at the wine kitchen was so spot on. The food was very nice and the presentation was just as nice. I will definitely go back again . I like how it's on the creek so there's things to see and do after or before dinner.
Insanely delicious food and the wine list is abundant! Service has always been phenomenal

For any who appreciate superb food, a diverse and creative beverage menu, and top notch service, look no further than The Wine Kitchen. My wife and I have enjoyed this restaurant for any and every occasion over the past five years, and we seize any opportunity to recommend it to other locals, entertain guests, or just drop in for a quick drink or dessert.  The entire team here caters to every want - whether a specific request for a special occasion, a dietary restriction or preference, or an accommodation for a party - they will ensure you have a memorable experience coupled with the best food that Downtown Frederick has to offer. The menu offerings are flawlessly executed by Chef Jeff and his team, and the dining room is managed with the utmost attention to detail by John and Laura. As a Long Island native, I recommend the duck in any preparation that the chef offers. For wine, you absolutely cannot go wrong with any of the flights.  We look forward to many more memorable evenings with friends, family, colleagues, and your wonderful staff. Cheers.
Great food,  awesome staff, great drinks
Still the best bone-in-ribeye my husband and I have ever had to date. We love coming here for special occasions. Can't wait until next time!
Great wine, delicious apple doughnut dessert, and friendly staff!!

I have absolutely no complaints nor negative comments. The food was cooked to perfection, the atmosphere was wonderful. And the staff was kind, helpful, and made me and my girlfriend feel incredibly comfortable. Our waitress felt like a friend, not just an employee at a restaurant. I highly reccomend trying everything I had there tonight.

It's not often you can say every part of your dining experience was spot on 100 percent!  Our waiter Tom was top notch!!  Knowledgeable in detail regarding drinks, menu items, specials and desserts!  It wasnt just our table, I observed him with others and he was checking in, engaging with the patrons, just frequent enough, but not over the top.  My friend and I both shared the mussels, ordered the fish special (amberjack, I believe from Hawaii), had amazing house special cocktail and had a wonderful peach special dessert!  The mussels were amazing and the broth preparation and garnish were different and so good!  The fish melted in our mouth. Cooked to perfection. The califlower vegetable was also delicious.  Honestly, this was the best fish, I've ever eaten and fish is my go too, since I dont eat meat.  Kudos to the chef, presentation and the food was excellent!  Kudos the pastry chef as well. Her desserts are not only beautiful, fresh ingredients, but taste amazing!! Save room!  The Wine Kitchen is a must, if you are foodie like me and enjoy a great meal and dont feel bad walking away paying for it too!!
Had the duck last night and as always it didn't disappoint. Food is always consistent, service good and atmosphere great!
Excellent food and service with amazing outdoor seating by the Creek!
Great food and atmosphere
Great restaurant and staff. We’ve been a couple times and it’s never let us down. Brunch is great. Make sure you try the corn meal pancakes.

Loved it here! We went to a nice weekend brunch and got to sit along the creek. Frederick has a dog costume contest apparently? So we got to see tons of cute dogs in costumes.  Kat our server was awesome! She was super attentive and friendly. We had a great time! We each did the $20 pick two lunch option which was fantastic. I live the mushroom strudel!

Went to this place for a late afternoon lunch. We sat outside (weather was perfect). My wife and I ordered cocktails (she had the Gin Fizz and I had the Boulevardier), both were fantastic. We split the beat salad and the burger. The staff split the salad and the burger for us without us asking. Both the salad and the burger were amazing...maybe even the best I have ever had. Service was exceptional. Will definitely be coming back here when we are in Frederick.
Friendly and efficient service. Amazing selection of wine from all over the world at all price ranges.  Outside seating is a plus.
I was honestly disappointed. The food wasn’t overly flavorful. Chicken was bland.
Outdoor seating is the best. Mexican BLT had fantastic toasted bread and contrasting textures moist sweet tomato and thick salty bacon.
Excellent food!

BLUF: I recommend going on a weekday.  Mybmother and I went on a Tuesday for early dinner, we sat outside and had a view of the creek.  It was a beautiful setting.  Our waiter, Justin was phenomenal!!! He was super attentive, polite, checked on us often and made suggestions when we asked.  He definitely gets 5 stars!!!  The food was 4 stars, I had the duck and although it was beautifully displayed the amount of food for the price was disproportionate, and the duck itself wasn't seasoned much.  My mother got a steak and enjoyed it very much.  We both got wine flights and enjoyed them.  I would go back, but not order the duck again.
Great food and ambience!
Wonderful and creative execution. The staff is knowledgeable, polite and helpful. The setting is a little rustic and charming.

I wish I lived in Frederick so I could enjoy this place more often. Fortunate circumstances allowed two visits this week for a group lunch and weekend dinner. No bad bites to be found. Peach gazpacho bright and flavorful. Mini tuna tartare tacos not mini in taste. A new favorite grilled octopus. Land and sea both equally delightful with the duck breast perfectly prepared and with great accompanying components. Wine suggestions were spot-on with a new viognier to search out for regular use. Dessert also impressed with beautiful classic combinations of chocolate and almonds. Can't wait for my next trip to Frederick!
Happy hour is very nice. Good selection of wines.
Slaps
Great food options. The wine flights are excellent. Lovely patio outside on the creek...great spot to sit on a day w good weather. Very good service.
Went from a good from a good waiter to a bad. Pricey.

My husband and I had reservations to try this restaurant.  Now for the Good, the Bad, and the Ugly:  Good:  We were seated quickly. The green beans were excellent.  Overall the food was satisfactory.  We opted not to have dessert for the reasons below.  Bad:  Service was very slow and almost nonexistent.  From the time we went in,  it took 1 1/2 hours to be served.  My husband is a pretty good tipper.  He gives the wait staff generally 40% - 50% if there are no problems.  Instead he gave 20%.  I would have left 15%.  I would say the service was the biggest drawback.  We both do not want to return because of it.  The place is incredibly noisy as it is all hard surfaces.  We couldn't even have a conversation.  Noise is something they can't do anything about but was a deal breaker for me.  Wine is over priced.  Ugly:  Part of my view from my table was an open storage area and a coat rack.  Really?  A door would have been nice or even a curtain.  View also included a booth and at the end of said booth was an area below the seat that was painted white with dirt all over it.  This was a birthday celebration and it fell flat.  We will drive to Bethesda or DC if we must to find great food and service.  Hopefully we can find a great Frederick restaurant.  The Wine Kitchen on the Creek was NOT even in the ballpark.
Second time here. Have had Brunch and Lunch. Good food, good atmosphere

Celebrated our first anniversary here, and was not disappointed. The atmosphere is very nice, a chic-rustic, very nice. The food was incredible, I had the duck. Their wine pairings were reasonably priced and decently portioned. A great place to go for a special occasion.

The wine was amazing and the food was delicious. My wife and I went here and I had the Gazpacho and main course of Diver Scallops. The complexity and taste of each dish was fantastic. Would definitely recommend this restaurant!

Ah, where to begin...  I ordered their Wagyu special of the night - the Ribeye Cap for $58 (which I requested medium rare).  When the steak arrived I cut through to ensure it was cooked properly and clearly noted it was completely raw in the middle.  Requested the waiter to fix the situation and they took my plate away.  Shockingly, a few minutes later they brought back my steak which i cut into - instead of preparing a new steak, they simply threw my existing pieces back on the grill.  That is terrible - anyone who knows steaks, understands you cannot cook a piece of meat two times.  Given my frustration, I requested to speak to the manager.  Instead of apologizing, their stance was that the steak is still cooking on the way out to the table - this is NO excuse for serving raw meat.  Additionally, have they forgotten a steak needs to rest for several minutes before serving?!  It was absolutely terrible that they tried to defend their raw steak.  I had to tell the manager that I should’ve gotten a new steak after being served a raw one - why should I be penalized for the chefs mistake for a $58 steak?  In the end, the manager did not even offer any reimbursement or to cover any drink or appetizer.  I wouldn’t write a negative review but this is the second occurrence at this restaurant - the first time the waiter dropped an entire pitcher of water on my fiancé, apologized and again, no mediation or resolution from management.  Piss poor management at this restaurant - which I hope they resolve immediately for their own sake.
My husband and I dined here recently and we loved it. The food is phenomenal and the service is top notch! Thank you WK for making our night special.
Great food, tasty plates and good atmosphere.
I love this place. Great views, great ambience, great service, great food.
Great food and atmosphere
Great food, GREAT service, and a great outdoor space to eat. Portion sizes are smaller (not tappas small) but just right.

Don't get the shrimp and grits here'-----Enough said !.!! ! If you order the mushroom strudel know that you are going to have to wait at least 20 minutes for it to be served. The server should make the customer aware of this when they order. The salad greens that were served  were past their time and were wilted.

We experienced excellent service from the busy and professional staff at the Wine Kitchen. The food was perfectly prepared and delicious. A curated wine selection is stellar. Thanks to the chef for awesome vegetarian options. We will return next time we're in Frederick.

My husband and I dined here for our wedding anniversary and everything was superb from the Champagne to the hand written card from the staff. The food is always phenomenal and the service is top notch! Thank you WK for making our night special.

Unfortunately, a bit of a let down from previous visits. Not the wait staff, they were great. Started with a flight of reds. Two were ok, one had oxidized. Offered to change it out for us which we welcomed. However, we were told that we were mistaken. Sorry, I'm familiar with what oxidized wine is like. Guess I made a mistake ordering a red on a summer day... That said, they brought me a different wine and it was ok. Ordered one of the Salmon specials and a burger. The Salmon was ok, nothing special though and a bit bland. The burger was a bit over done. Had a new menu "for the season." Didn't really see anything that we wanted and missed the old menu. Sad, as I knew I could count on taking guests to the WK. Well, as Meatloaf said, "2 out of 3 ain't bad." Hope this was an exception, not the new norm.  Visited The Wine Kitchen again. Now using compostable containers for take home leftovers!!! EXCELLENT. Oh, and the food was delicious, again! Steak, duck, burgers, all great.  A limited menu, but in a good way. I had the pastrami sandwich. Was the best pastrami sandwich I've had in many years. Simply put, the food is fantastic. They also offer an innovative choice of wine flights. Fun to try a selection. Can't wait to try the rest! We'll surely return.
Another wonderful meal. Our waiter Noah really took care of us.
My favorite restaurant in Frederick.

Tiny food. Tuna tacos were delicious but, very small portions. My friend had the halibut, vegetables, and potatoes. The potatoes were tough and cooked in some very sour, tangy sauce. Fish was decent. Green fried tomatoes were delicious. Wine and cocktails were the icing on the cake.
Food quality is consistently very good
One of my go-to places to grab some food. awesome location, always clean, and excellent service. I recommend this place!
Food and wine were excellent.

My husband and I had the duck, swordfish, chocolate almond dessert, beet carpaccio, and buffalo chicken fries and every bite was DELICIOUS. Flavors were so vibrant and bold, every dish was such a treat. Even the dishes that we expected to be a little too rich/heavy we’re light and delicious. Nothing too greasy or overpowering. Just well balanced flavors and high quality food. Definitely worth the money for a special occasion or a night on the town!
Amazing meal
Everything from the service, to the food, to the view was excellent.
Food is always fabulous.  Nice bottle of wine, at a good price, very low markup.  We had the Steak Flights to eat.  Ser ice was excellet.
Good selection of wine! Took my wife here for our anniversary and it was perfect!
Food and service was great!
Fabulous dinner, great service. Highly recommend.
Morgan!

I love this place! I’m taking there my friends, boyfriend, family, everyone will find something good for themselves! The food is very good, always nicely served. The wine is very worth of trying, not expensive, this same thing about their cocktails. I recommend sitting inside as much as outside during warmer weather. Very vibrant and nice place to go to.
Need I say more?

We LOVE the Wine Kitchen.... usually. Tonight we waited for half an hour and didn’t even get a drink! We asked our waitress, Morgan, for a minute to look over the menu and she never returned. We waited and waited, and after 30 minutes decided to just leave! We have never had that kind of service at this establishment before. Wine Kitchen, please, you have an amazing menu, amazing venu, and amazing wine selection, do something about your servers. Very disappointing :(

My gf surprised me with my bday dinner here. I just want to start off with the cook and food 5 stars. But service very slow. We ordered a bottle of wine that never came out until we had to ask after our starters came out. After asking the bottle of wine still did t come out until we were almost done with our starters. Again we asked. Over all service from our server 1 star. The food on the other hand amazing. The food will being us back, but we will not book this place for a special event. We usually like to oder 1 or 2 bottles of wine and 1 to go if the restaurant allows. In this case we were left sitting to drink water long into our food.
Fun atmosphere, great service, delicious food.
Food was fantastic.

Nice place.. Not fantastic, but nice. The food was more pretty than good and a bit higher price than places I've had higher a quality dinner. The service was EXCELLENT. They really were attentive and polite. The view was nice on the creek, but it started to rain so we moved inside. No available seats so we ate at the bar (not a problem for my wife and I.)  *Octopus - Beautiful looking presentation,  way overcooked and rubbery.  We eat this every place we can find it and purposely hunt restaurants that have it on the menu.  *Fried Green Tomatoes - Awesome! Some of the best I've had. Perfectly cooked and served simply.  Get these when you go.  *Filet - Excellent.  Like butter. Cooked perfectly.  *Scallops - Cooked perfectly. Great flavor. (Went well with the steak. My wife and I split the 2 entrees).  Drinks..  Despite the name I stuck with bourbon/ryes and they have a nice selection of Whistle pig. Prices are a bit higher than I'm used to seeing, but not totally over board.  We might come back. We might not. It's worth a try and their other food looked nice.. but I wasn't blown away and there are a lot of other options around to try before I give TWK another chance.
The food was amazing, especially the filet. The manager (didn’t catch his name) went above and beyond to make sure we had everything we needed. Sat outside and atmosphere was beautiful. Loved it!
My husband and I had a fantastic experience!

The food was excellent.  My wife had the scallops which were amazing.  I had steak which was very good but not as good as the scallops.  Or waitress was awesome.  She was attentive and very nice.  Wonderful dinner and evening!

Good food for the most part, very expensive (Be prepared to drop  $$$ per person, or almost that) for the amount but high quality... they apparently shut down the full menu during certain hours which was slightly annoying but not terrible since we could order drinks and starters, just not regular menu items till 4:30pm.. The desserts were a bit of a let down, maybe include more of a description of them so people aren't totally confused when it comes out. It's worth at least going once...

30+ minutes sitting at the bar and still haven't had a chance to place my food order. Drink is empty. I guess I will have to leave and go somewhere else for food. I thought this place served food but apparently they do not. At least that's my experience today.

Like a heathen and a complete rookie move, I only took a photo of the appetizer and desert. But that speaks solely on how amazing it was, both aesthetically and in flavor. We started with the pick six charcuterie plate. Finally convinced my wife to try Foie gras, at about the 10 o’clock position with a red wine reduction on top. She was impressed. The accompaniments were perfectly paired. My wife had the scallops and I had a beet salad and pappardelle pasta. They were so beautiful, and so amazingly tasty. We ordered the peanut butter and banana deconstructed pie. It was so decadent and rich. The perfect balance of texture and flavors to please the whole mouth. Loved this wonderful evening with my wife.
Reasonably priced and great to sit outside on a nice evening.

The food is really good, we had quiche and appetizers since it was Easter brunch and we didn't have a reservation, but we made the most of it. Staff was great and the bubbly is always uplifting. I really like sitting outside here.
Excellent food and service

Last night, my husband, Bill and I went there for the 8th anniversary of the day we met. We reserved a few weeks ago and used a gift certificate for a 3 course wine-paired dinner for 2.  Our highest complements to the daytime bartender, Laura,who poured us two glasses of Kava (sp?) to begin our celebration; the chef, Jeff Beard, for the delectable cuisine; our undying gratitude for being treated like royalty by the manager on duty,  Justin, who was our server;  and we have to thank the young man keeping our water filled throughout the entire evening as well.  Kudos to the Wine Kitchen on the Creek for giving us one of our best anniversary dinners to date!

Probably the best wine selection in town.  The menu spans all price levels from burgers to filet.   Food is excellent.  Outdoor dining on a nice evening overlooking Carol creek may be the best dining experience in town.
Fantastic food!

We had wonderful food & wine with a large group for business dinner.  I had the filet and it was perfectly prepared. We were pleased that all of the food came out at same time and everyone enjoyed their meal.

The wait staff was very polite and never had me feeling like I was waiting around. I ordered the chicken mole. The flavors were subtle but interesting.I highly recommend their charcuterie selection, as well. The wine, as you would expect, was well recommended and delicious. We went on a rainy day so the atmosphere felt very cozy and inviting.
I will add another 5 star review. I attended a meeting that was held in their private room. It was very comfortable and the lunch they offered was delicious. Highly recommend.
Way expensive. Good service. Passable food.

I've been here a lot and sometimes its amazing and sometimes I leave saying that I'm never going back.  I just can't figure this place out.  I've had times were the service was stellar, and food matched the service.  They even changed out the wines in my flight if I didn't care for one.  Then other times I couldn't get my water refilled and my order came out wrong and the server told me I should of been more clear while giving him my order.  I love going to the wine kitchen but we often joke about what adventure awaits us before we go.  Everything is more fun with wine however!
Wonderful food, great service!!
Went for sunday brunch. Great location by canal, nice rustic space, very attentive service. Food was great quality but helpings were a little light IMHO. Very good all around though.
I keep my stuff here and each time I come back it's still there and its dry. What else do you possibly want.
Love the food, ambiance and the service.
First time eating here.  Have a very nice food selection not to mention a wine selection. It has a very nice location sitting right on the canal
Classy and delicious! Was here for an early business dinner and we were both impressed. Excellent quality and service.

I'm not sure what happened to this place. It used to be a reliable choice for high quality dishes. Last night the service was non existent and food (short rib - $32) was comparable to home cooking. We went over 20 minutes without service at one point with no water at the table. I won't be going back again or recommending to anyone I know.
Food was exceptional!
The best of the best! Always consistently delicious food. And top notch service everytime.
Jeff the chef never disappoints!  Went here for restaurant week and it was fabulous!  Best restaurant in Frederick hands down!  Keep up the good work

I actually reviewed this place a couple years ago at 5 stars.  Our visit last week was definitely not that.  I actually ordered the same thing I did then and the food was just not prepared as well.   I think I said this was one of the top places in Frederick at that time, but it was very much solidly in the middle now, but still with a top end price.  Service was good and attentive, but all the details were missing.  No longer our go-to special occasion spot.
Long wait for food, but great atmosphere.  Will definitely go back again.
Always a great meal. The Wagyu Ribeyes were fantastic tonight. Excellent cocktails and local flights too.

Walked in for a few glasses of wine. No seats available in the bar area and the hostess would not let us sit in the dining area which was completely empty. There was 4 of us and we were planning on having a couple glasses of wine each and appetizers.  We walked out.
Beautiful setting for groups. Good wine selection. $$$

The selection of food is limited and expensive but the quality is top notch. The selection of wine flights is satisfying as well! The laid back and cozy atmosphere makes this place great for special occasions.

What a treat, and on the canal, in walking distance of downtown.  Steak and fry happy hr apitizer... buy 2!   Superior staff and food.   Fast service.  Really nice modern decor and fireplace.  Love wine selection.
Food was great service was excellent
Amazing out server Tim was very nice!
Love the wine kitchen. I get my food hot and quick.
Creative chefs and mixologists! Great value at happy hour! The pork-belly rolls, duck spring rolls, and fried oysters we're all delicious, as was the cocktail.
Amazing Ambience, great food, great atmosphere, great music, great service, just an all around great experience, came with my wife on a date and we had a great time. Definitely will come back.

If the rating was based solely on taste then it would be higher. We found this place significantly over priced based on portion side. If we hadn't gotten muliple appitizers I would have had to eat when I got home. I had the sablefish which was maybe 4oz that came with potatoes which was maybe a 1/4 of a whole potato. The only thing that wasn't over priced was the wine and the rib eye. I would go back if you paid for what is was really worth. Overall the taste of everything we got was very good.
Fantastic scallops, beets salad, and rock fish! The fried green tomatoes were unremarkable. Ask for Laura as your waitress - she was a hoot!!
While the wine kitchen is always delicious it's quite expensive. $27 for 4 diver scallops. Youch.
Food was very good although mac and cheese entree was a rather small.  Service was not so good. There at switch between lunch and dinner so staffing have been low.
Had my work Christmas party  here. The food was delicious, the party room was goregous and it was such a nice atmosphere!

Awesome incredible ambience and dining experience on Saturday before Christmas. The place was packed but they team worked their way to success. The short ribs and lamb were sooo good and paired with a fair priced bottle of Merlot. Go here when in Frederick!
Modern American cuisine with a hint of gastropub. Flavorful deconstructed menu items with excellent food presentation. The staff provides excellent service with a smile
Great food and wine list.. laid back atmosphere
Delicious. A little on the pricey side. But worth it

Superior service, delicious food, wonderful wine. On a cold night, it was a welcoming and warm place to be. The food was done perfect along with a very helpful service crew. Best part is, if you can't commit to a certain wine, you can choose your own flights!!
Service was above and beyond

Came here for our anniversary and was by far the best meal I've had in months. The staff was absolutely amazing. We got charcuterie, wine flights, the burger (Omg) and duck... We'll be back here for sure sooner rather than later.
Bloody Mary's are amazing. Food took a while but it was tasty.
Another fabulous meal.  Great wine recommendation from John the manager. The mussels are great, you'll want extra bread for the broth.
Wonderful place with a really comfortable feel.

Came here after a night on the town and found a place I will visit again. The ambiance was trendy but subtle and the wine selection was vast. I didn't look at the dinner menu extensively, but it did seem very well put together. Great overall experience.

Went for the first time and it was outstanding in every way. Going back tonight (the next day)! The wine and food was excellent, especially the beef. It was some of the best I've had and the most flavorful. I really enjoyed all courses and highly recommend the place.
Very well prepared dishes. Knowledgeable staff and great atmosphere. Would go back whenever I had the opportunity.
This is definitely a brunch dream, the ceasar is the best is town. The Benedict options are delicious, and love the seasonal twists they add in. Looking forward to Fall
Great food, good selection of wine and a few well crafted mixed beverages. The service has also has always been very delightful and accommodating. One of the nicer places to eat when in town, enjoy!

We had a late lunch and were splitting an 8oz. Burger and the Heirloom Tomato Salad. Best burger in a long time, wonderful,  fresh, Heirloom Tomato Salad. Attentive service. We’ll be back soon!  Great spot right on Carroll Creek Pedestrian Mall, and around the corner from public parking. One of the best restaurants in Frederick.
Service was great and was nice sitting on the canal. Some of the food was a miss but will definitely try again.
Amazing food and atmosphere
We finally moved to Fredrick and we have been dining here once a week because the food is delicious and comes with outstanding customer service.
Good food specials during happy hour. Like most bar atmospheres, can get extremely loud and difficult to hear others at your table if seated near the bar.
Love this place. Been here 4 times, stellar meal and service every time.
Great place one of the best happy hours in downtown Frederick. Beautiful view right on the river great service great ambiance great place.
Brunch was yummy Would def come back here!
The vegan and vegetarian dishes, desert was awesome! Great service too. 💚
Great happy hour,  sometimes great service,  sometimes not.  Good location.
Eclectic setting with a twist of European flare.
The food was outstanding, and service was phenomenal. Very professional waiter who timed service wonderfully.
Good food. Good service.

Great atmosphere with outdoor seating right on the creek.  Staff is very helpful and attentive.  Food was fantastic, I had the dry aged filet whose flavor was amazing.  Cooked to rare and they did in excellent job of that, was extremely tender and again the flavor was top notch.  Appetizers and side dishes were great as well.  Can't wait to go back and try more
Great wine and they have Foie Gras! Service food and atmosphere os always wonderful. If you are in the area and appreciate great food and drink this is the spot for you!
Food and service have been first rate for both lunch and dinner. The wine and cocktail selection are well thought out with reasonable prices. It's professionally well run.
Food is good but way over priced. Been to much better places.
Great food!
Great!!
Expensive but excellent.
Amazing restaurant in beautiful Frederick. Their $27 prix fixed breakfast was delicious!
Great atmosphere. Typical expensive high level cuisine that tastes great. Outdoor seating was in rough shape.
Delicious food and great spot outside on the creek!
Excellent food and menu. Drinks were original and delicious
Our first time here the place was nice the food  was delicious ,price ok the nice part about it was the location you get to take a walk around the town.
Small portions but good food. Champagne list is limited. But of course that is a first world problem

Amazing food.  Although guy at door stereotyped me n made me sit at bar bc I look young and was by myself place was empty and empty when I left... But bartenders did everything perfect so cant be mad... get better hair cut buddy... you know who you are.
GREAT food and lovely outside patio. $20 2 course lunch menu was a good deal and includes everything on the menu.
24-hour short rib is just yummy, tender - oh yeah, the wine is good too.
Yum...everything here is excellent
Great experience with this restaurant. They use high quality materials.
Great location on the creek, beautiful view, alfresco dining, good food.
Great spot for a date!
Just an awesome meal from start to finish. Tuna Tacos, Waygu, an affordable bottle of Spanish wine. I like it!

Great selection of quality wines! Great food! Service was very good; no rush; good recommendations on food and wine choices. Their special of the night had duck, Waygu and rabbit in the place. Very tasty 😋.

Went here for a date night on a Friday as a last minute decision. Didn't disappoint and ended up being very impressed. Their wine menu and the delivery of the wine is great. You get a little piece of paper explaining the wine, where it came from, etc. We got a cheese plate which was exceptional. This seems like a great place for a charcuterie plate if you want to add in meats, etc. For dinner I decided on the cola marinated sirloin, different but good. My boyfriend got the roseda farm burger which he really liked a lot. Definitely would return again, especially for the excellent service.

Went here for Frederick Restaurant Week and it was a  Great experience! Food was very good drinks were Good! I would definitely come back again!  I didn't have wine but their selection of wine as awesome as really cool that offer flights wine too. Need to try that next.
Great service and food
Great food and drinks.
Just had a wine flight but it was good and the servers were incredibly nice.

There is a lot to like here.  The food quality is top notch, the atmosphere pleasant, and the service friendly.  But said service also tends to get scatter-brained once the business level gets to "moderate", and the offerings are pricey with a capital P.  Their "half off bar food" happy hour seems like a great bargain until you discover the miniscule size of the portions, though again, really good.  More a special occasion place than a regular haunt for us plebeians who have to watch our money carefully, it gets enough right to be worth an occasional trip but, for what it charges, could (and definitely should) do better.
Great food and desserts!!!

Always a favorite place to spend a happy hour. Great wine selection and friendly staff. My only criticism is the menu obsession with pork. A few more vegetarian or even pescetarian options for snacks would be fantastic.
The food was so good and I loved the wine flights.
Great service and over all well prepared food. I few minor shortcomings in the preparation of a white bean and red bell pepper purée. Fried green tomatoes were terrific.
Fantastic visit as always. Discovered a new favorite wine by having one of the flights.
We've been there a couple of times an have really enjoyed the experience. The staff have been very helpful with suggestions, as well as dietary accommodations. Their hoecakes were super tasty!
Very friendly service. Beautiful setting. Great food and wine!
Food was good. Service excellent. Great staff.
Excellent for wine and snacks with friends, especially if you can sit outside and people watch.
Very nice wine bar and savory foods. Great service
THIS PLACE 👌🏽✔💯
Great food, great drinks! Staff was super friendly, fun and helpful! If I didn't live so far away I would be here more often!
5 stars for the Yummy food 5 stars for the staff and management 5 stars for the atmosphere
Hit or miss. Great atmosphere. Love the French press coffee.
Excellent food and service!
Awesome!   Portions are jusr perfect!   Service was efficient, pleasant, casual not stuffy.   Food was outrageously delicious.   Will definitely return.
Delicious food and a great selection of wine.
Great foid, and Atmosphere,  but the  service is a bit slow
Great place to go with my wife. They always have different things to offer and the charchuterie is great.
Delicious food, great drinks, and outstanding service.
Always wonderful!

Excellent service.  Attentive but not intrusive, and they quietly paid attention to let us enjoy the meal the way we wanted it.  Great wine list by the glass, and intriguing tasting trios.  The food was amazing, from starters to entrees to coffee.  The duck, oh my goodness, the duck.  Food alone is top 2 or 3 in Frederick, which if you know the area is actually saying something, plus nice un-stuffy atmosphere (dress up some jeans and you're fine here) and nice location.   Highly recommended.
Variety of exquisite wines 👌
A good place to grab appetizers and, of course, wine!

I've been here for brunch and dinner and both times I was blown away. Fantastic food and wine selection. The wine cards are incredibly cheesy however and kinda takes away from what the taster feels about the wine themselves. I feel like they are unnecessary. A little pricey so I can't come often but you certainly get what you pay for.  Can't wait till patio season starts. I'll definitely be back once it's warmer out.
Had Shane as our waiter and he was fantastic. Food was delicious and we'll portioned. Great selection of wine as well. Definitely will be back.

Wow. Just wow. Every time my husband and I dine here we are blown away. The whiskey flights, the red wine flights, and don’t even get me started on that my-tastebuds-explode-because-it’s-so-amazing Coca Cola sirloin. Don’t even waste your …
Food just melts in your mouth...best steak we have ever had! Wines..wonderful

Great place. Great food. Have eaten there several times before. However, be careful if you bring a birthday cake in vs. buying desert  from restaurant. Was told no problem when called in advance.  Staff is not fully aware of policy, how to apply it when appropriate, or they are not telling customers of mandatory $3 per person plating charge until after the fact and you get the bill. We cut the cake ourselves and not everyone ate the cake.  I understand there is a cost to clean a plate, but this a bit of pure greed and high profit.  While it was Valentine's Day late in the evening, extra time at table was not the issue as no one was waiting for the table and other tables were empty.  Felt a bit deceived.
Always a great meal, with great wine to go with!
Tim, the bartender, sweet, cute, and professional!  Great atmosphere and selections!

Excellent service..lovely location by the water. Everything was plated beautifully...and tasted even better than it looked! Salt beakers were fun. (Really didn’t even need them everything was seasoned and cooked wonderfully) a superb selection of wines and flights. End by sharing a dessert..they are beautiful and you will be so glad you didn’t miss the experience.  This is definitely a “don’t miss”
Food was delicious
Food and service were awesome!  Would definitely go back.
This place was amazing. Great food, and the ora was really nice.

Amazing! My husband couldn’t stop talking about how delicious everything was! We didn’t make reservations so they asked us if it was okay if we were done by 6 (it was around 4pm) due to Valentine’s Day week. We should of known better but we were lucky! Our waitress, V, was fantastic! Beautiful girl and awesome personality (not just with us-she was great with all the tables around us). We had a Frederick mule and a pomegranate cosmopolitan to drink. Delicious! Mussels and beet salad as appetizers—whoever thought of combining cocoa cardamom with beets is a genius of taste buds! My husband had the duck breast and I had rockfish and we both loved it! I often need to use salt&pepper shakers but I know why they weren’t present at the table: everything was seasoned perfectly! My husband doesn’t like sweets so I got the apple cake for myself! I’m not a big fan of chamomile (it was topped with chamomile ice cream) but the combination of the ingredients made it a great dessert! Definitely will be back! And definitely will recommend to friends and family!
Most definitely my favorite place in downtown Frederick. The food is wonderful and the service is outstanding
Favorite restaurant anywhere.
Great staff, great atmosphere, and the food was incredible. We definitely will be back soon!
It was amazing!!!!!
Great food and wine
Awesome food, service and wine selections!

This is my second time dining at this restaurant and although the food and service is great, our experience was ruined by how cold it was inside the restaurant. I'm not sure if it was cold in every part but we were seated next to a window and all of our feet were freezing to the point that we had to bring our legs up off the floor to continue eating. Some of my party never took their jackets off.  We mentioned to our server and he was apologetic and nice but it wasn't something he had control over so unfortunately we had to push through it. I hope they figure it out during this cold winter but even though I enjoy their food I might wait until spring to visit them again.
Overpriced and very modern not for me

The food is fresh tasting. They like to put their own spin on traditional dishes and the kitchen does an excellent job. The wine choices are diversified and we'll thought out. This service was an issue and a large negative. Apparently our server knows a lot of regular customers and he spent almost all of his time with them. We do prefer not to be rushed so that was good but being constantly ignored can be a real negative on an otherwise good meal.

Just enjoyed my Anniversary dinner at this fine establishment. The food was delicious, the ambiance was perfect and I would highly recommend it to anyone I know. They were courteous enough to greet us with free champagne. 5 HUGE STARS.....we will be back.
Great food.  Great drinks. Great service. My favorite place to eat in Frederick.
Love this place
Very limited options for vegetarians
Great service and wonderful food, the best in frederick
I've been here for brunch and dinner and I had a pleasant experience. The food was delicious and the  service was great.
I had the chicken pot pie special and it was awesome! Also had the Primal Red wine tasting...go Eagle Glen Merlot! Shane and team were helpful and so friendly!
Excellent choice of wines and fabulous happy hour specials with perfect food.
wow the finest wagyu steaks ever. Every bite ofnit was heavenly. I m probably going back to it pretty soon. A tad expensive but then again it is a fine dining establishment
Great food and good wines. A bit on the expensive side, but worth it once in a while. The cheese and array of cold cuts and spreads is not to be missed.

A perfect lunch: excellent tuna fish tacos as a starter and an expertly cooked cod (special of the day: fish and chips). Add to that lots of good wine choices and we'll trained, friendly and efficient service. Highly recommend the place for any ocassion.
WOW.......that is all!
Excellent
Although crowded at times, it's crowded for a reason. Amazing food with a wine selection that can't be beat.
Foot is always fantastic, including a great wine selection.  Service was average.
Perfect steaks everytime. Impeccable service and a well curated wine list.
Wonderful brunch. Delish!
Another great afternoon at the Wine Kitchen On the Creek!!!!
Always a good experience here. Wonderful food and drinks.

The wine kitchen is one (three) of my favorite restaurants in the area. We go to the Leesburg one a lot because it's closer, but they are all great. Always wonderful and friendly staff. The food is always delicious and the wine and wine flights are great.
Nice setting by the water in downtown Frederick. Service and food were good but just came across lacking some personality.
Delicious food and drinks, plus there is outdoor seating!
Excellent food and service. They never disappoint.

We sampled some brunch fare during the Taste of Frederick and went back for dinner.  Our party of four all enjoyed our meal. There was a nice selection of wine and beer.  Three of the entree items were no longer available but since the …
Excellent food, excellent service. Cant ask for anything else
Great food, great service, delicious wine.
